    <h1 class="text-center">About the 40 Book Challenge</h1>

    <h2 class="text-center">Overview</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Set a goal to read 40 books by the date set by your teacher.</li>
            <ul>
                <li>TRY YOUR BEST!</li>
                <li>It’s okay if you don’t make it to 40. We will celebrate at 20, 30, & 40!</li>
            </ul>
        <li>Try something new!  See the genre requirements for the different genres you’ll need to read for this challenge. You can read the genres in any order.
        </li>
        <li>Pick books at your independent reading level.  (“Just Right” or “Good Fit” books)</li>
        <li>Everybody reads here!  Everybody is a reader!</li>
        <li>What you read is your choice ….. whatever you want …. you pick!</li>
        <li>You may listen to audio versions of a book and follow along in the printed book for up to 10 books.</li>
        <li>Picture books may count for certain genres, must have teacher approval.</li>
        <li>You may count books you read in class, books from home, books from the public library, books from our classroom library, books from our school media center.</li>
        <li>Fiction books over 250 pages can be counted as 2 books.</li>
        <li>Nonfiction books over 100 pages may be counted as 2 books.</li>
        <li>You may not count books that you’ve read in the past.</li>
        <li>You may “abandon” a book that is not holding your interest, but it will not count toward your total.</li>
        <li>You may listen to audio versions of a book and follow along in the printed book for up to 10 books.</li>
    </ul>

