    <section>
        <h3 class="text-center">Q & A</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>What books should I read?
                <ul>
                    <li>You may choose any books that have at least 100 pages in any of the genres on the required genre list.</li>
                    <li>“Just Right” or “Good Fit” books</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>What if I don’t know where to start?
                <ul>
                    <li>If you don’t know where to start, your teacher will be happy to offer suggestions based on what you like…..Teachers love to chat about books!</li>
                    <li>Your teacher will start doing weekly book previews, where he/she will share recommendations for some of his/her favorite books.</li>
                    <li>A classmate might share a book that he/she is reading that he/she enjoyed.</li>
                    <li>Eventually, your classmates will share book reviews about the books they’re reading to give you ideas.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>How will you know that I am reading?
                <ul>
                    <li>You are required to complete a reading response entry in your reading notebook at least once per week.
                    </li>
                    <li>This is due on check-in dates your teacher will set, but you can complete it before those days if you like.</li>
                    <li>You will create book reviews for the books you’re reading</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>What happens when I reach my goal?
                <ul>
                    <li>You will love reading so much by then that you will just keep on going!</li>
                    <li>You’ll be a lifelong reader!</li>
                    <li>You’ll be so proud of yourself for all your hard work!</li>
                    <li>Your teacher will be very proud of you for all your hard work!</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h4 class="text-center">I PICK</h4>
